{"id":"elmalg-solvelin_both-003","cid":"ELMALG","topic":"Linear Equations and Inequalities","subtopic":"Variables on both sides","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"Solve for x: {m1}x + {b1} = {m2}x + {b2}. (Hint: m1 > m2 here, so collect x terms on the left.)","params":{"m1":{"type":"int","min":5,"max":12},"b1":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":6},"m2":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":4},"b2":{"type":"int","min":10,"max":30}},"answer_expr":"solvelin_both","steps":["Subtract {m2}x from both sides: ({m1} - {m2})x + {b1} = {b2}.","Subtract {b1}: {lhs_m}x = {rhs_diff}.","Divide by {lhs_m}: x = {answer_solvelin_both}."],"tags":["elementary-algebra","linear-equation","variables-both-sides"]}
